 <P>
<head><H4>INTERNET DIARY DAY 10  </H4>
 
<br>9th May 1995</head><body>
<P>We are now into our second week on the Brent Spar, the oil
storage platform that Shell wants to sink in the Atlantic. We are
finally becoming more comfortable in our new surroundings. The
idea of living on a floating polluted island is not a pleasant
prospect but we have now firmly set this before us.
Since the construction of our wind generator above on the heli
deck and the increasing media interest surrounding our stay,
the morale of crew members has reached a satisfactory level and
the  mood is positive.
<P>The SPAR sways constantly, reminding us of our location and
the risks. Outside the temperature is a low 5 deg.C, not European
summer-like at all. Heating one room to a comfortable level is
now possible and that has been warmly welcomed.
<P>Our food supplies are still very substantial on board, with an
excellent French cook to keep us going. It is still difficult
to keep clean, with salt water for washing. As you look around
the dinner table you see ever longer beards looking back at
you! After 10 days we all could do with a hot bath, but that
is just a small sacrifice under the circumstances. The word
"Squatters" has been used in the press, perhaps this is
something along those lines. However how many squats have a
satellite phone/fax/e-mail communications?
So we continue our "sit in" for the common goal...
 
<P>DON'T DUMP THE SPAR...
 
