<head><H4>Diary - May 10 </H4>
</head><body>
 
<P>The hectic stress of the first few days is slowly changing to 
more
laborious activity. Every day there are  new things to build or
existing things which have to be repaired. It's incredible how
much equipment we have pulled onto the platform - the realisation
dawned on me slowly since we have now unpacked most of it.
 
<P>The atmosphere and the relationship between the crew is 
extremely
good. Unfortunately, it takes me a while to understand some of
the conversations because my English is  not very good - but it
is improving every day. Yesterday there was a very strong wind
and it was impressive to be on the heli-deck in the storm. There
is a marvellous 360 degrees view of the surroundings from up
there.
 
<P>Thanks to the excellent food that our excellent cook cooks for us 
- a warm
meal twice a day - I am definitely going to put on weight during
my stay!
