<html><head><P><H4>WRITE TO THE CHAIRMAN OF SHELL UK</H4>
</head><body>

<P>You can contact to the chairman of Shell UK and voice your concern about
the Shell's proposed dumping of the Brent Spar and the precedent it sets
for the oil companies in the future to dispose of the other 400+ fixed
oil and gas platforms currently in the North Sea. 

<P>You may like to ask him how reconciles this environmentally irresponsible
action with the aims of the Shell Environmental Trust.  

<pre>
Write To:  Christopher Fay,
           Chairman,
           Shell UK Ltd,
           Shell Mex House,
           The Strand,
           London,
           WC2R 0DX.
           United Kingdom

Or Phone: +44 (0)171 257 3000

Or Fax:   +44 (0)171 257 3939
</pre>
<HR><H4>WRITE TO YOUR GOVERNMENT AND DEMAND THAT THE NORTH SEA
CONFERENCE ELIMINATES ALL TOXIC WASTE DISCHARGES AND
IMPLEMENTS CLEAN PRODUCTION.</H4>

<P>Below is a draft letter you can use to send to your government
(Environment Ministers, European Parliament members or other
elected officials.



<P>NAME LETTER IS TO
<br>ADDRESS
<br>COUNTRY

<P>DATE HERE


<P>Dear________,

<P>As the North Sea ministers prepare to meet in Denmark in early
June, I am writing to ask you to take strong and urgent action
to end the destruction of this diverse ecosystem on which we
depend.

<P>As you are preparing to attend this meeting, the oil company
Shell has permission to scuttle and dump a toxic oil
platform into the waters of the North Sea.  This is a sign
of the lack of concern and understanding of the need to protect
one of our most valuable resources -- the North Sea.

<P>I understand that the North Sea ministers will consider
eliminating toxic production at source and therefore toxic
discharges into the North Sea.  I urge you to move forward with
this proposal and to strongly support these efforts.

<P>All of the North Sea countries depend equally on clean air water
and sea of our environment.  The decision to protect the North
Sea environment rests with you.  Please work for its protection.


<P>Sincerely,
<P>


Your name here
