<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Greenpeace: CLIMATE CHANGE AND GLOBAL INFECTIOUS DISEASE THREATS</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="../impactsban.gif" ALT="Health Impacts - Greenpeace"></A><A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="erwinban.gif" ALT="Erwin Report"></A><BR><B><I>Medical Journal of Australia</I>, vol.163, 1995, pp. 570-574.<BR>By: Erwin Jackson, Climate Impacts Specialist, Greenpeace International</B></P><HR WIDTH=85%>	<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Index</H2><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><P ALIGN=CENTER>1. <A HREF="1erwin.html">Introduction</A><BR>2. <A HREF="2erwin.html">Human-Induced Climate Change</A><BR>3. <A HREF="3erwin.html">Climate Change and Emerging Infectious Diseases</A><BR>4. <A HREF="4erwin.html">The Role of Health Organisations</A><BR>5. <A HREF="5erwin.html">Conclusion/Acknowledgements</A><BR></P></P></FONT><HR WIDTH=85%><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="../impactsgp.gif" ALT="Greenpeace"><FONT SIZE=-1><B>Address Correspondence to: </B><BR>Erwin Jackson, Climate Impacts Unit,<BR>Greenpeace International,<BR>c/o PO Box 800, Surry Hills, NSW 2010.<BR>Ph:+61 (0)2 211 4066 Fx: +61 (0)2 211 4123 <BR>E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:erwinj@mail.peg.apc.org">erwinj@mail.peg.apc.org</A><BR></FONT></BODY></HTML>
