<IMG SRC="floodhead.gif" ALT="GREENPEACE: Climate Change and River Flooding">
</P>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<HR WIDTH=80%>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>3.	GCM PROJECTIONS AND GLOBAL TRENDS IN RAINFALL
</H1>


In recent years, an impressive pile of reports has been published on changes in 
the climate as predicted by GCMs. An effort has been made here to extract the 
most recent information. After describing some of their characteristics, the review 
starts with the findings of transient global climate simulations and relevant 
results of mixed-layer models. (Results of regional-scale modelling will be 
summarised separately.) To compare, information on trends in rainfall on the 
global scale is given. 
<HR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="2-2.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="gpdotbk.gif" ALT="Go Back"></A>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="gpdotup.gif" ALT="Go Home"></A> 
<A HREF="3-1.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="gpdotfd.gif" ALT="Go Forward"></A> 
</P>
<HR> 
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT04-B25-138</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA082-000568-B041-286</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://greenpeace.org:80/~climate/flood_report/3-1.html 193.67.176.1 19970103182519 text/html 4696
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
