<B>Footnotes:</B><BR>
<A NAME="f1">*</A> The eruption of Mt. Pinatubo on the Philippines in June 1991 is thought to have 
caused a tropospheric cooling of about 0.5oC. However, its effects have worn off by 
1994. <A HREF="3-2.html#r1">Return</A>
</FONT SIZE>

