<B>Footnotes:</B><BR>
<A NAME="f1">*</A> For the European continent, three major circulations can be distinguished: 
<OL>
<LI> zonal circulations, with westerly winds and, in general, much rainfall 
(cyclone tracks from the eastern North Atlantic Ocean to the European 
continent);
<LI> meridional circulations, with stationary, blocking, high pressure centres at 
Central Europe, and mostly dry weather;
<LI> half-meridional circulations, with northwestern and southwestern winds. <A HREF="4-1.html#r1">Return</A>
</OL>

