<HEAD>
<TITLE>2020 - The Future if Berlin Summit Succeeds</TITLE>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="2020genhead.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Climate News"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>OPEC disbanded</FONT SIZE><BR>
<I>
Organisation of Hydrogen Exporting Countries founded
</I>
</P>
<BR>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<HR WIDTH=80%>
<P>



OPEC has disbanded itself at a historic meeting in Geneva. At the same
meeting representatives of all the former oil-exporting member states
founded the Organisation for Hydrogen Exporting Countries, OHEC. At its
end OPEC had been producing over 95 per cent of its energy exports with
hydrogen from energy obtained from the sun. In Saudi Arabia alone 
some 4,000 square miles of desert are bordered by photovoltaic panels. 
For some years now oil has only been extracted in small quantities for
special plastics and medicinal products. 
<P>
The Saudi Arabian Energy
Minister, Schams El Arab, said in Geneva that the turning point in
OPEC's energy policy began to made shortly before the Climate
Conference in Berlin in 1995. "We had no other choice. Either we had to
concentrate on alternative energies or go under, because it was no
longer possible to sell oil in large quantities."
