<HEAD>
<TITLE>2020 - The Future if Berlin Summit Succeeds</TITLE>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="2020genhead.gif" ALT="Greenpeace Climate News"><BR>
</P>
</HEAD>
<P>
<BODY>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+3>News In Brief</FONT SIZE><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER>
<I>
 <A HREF="briefgood.html#a3">Transport Prize Goes to Mexico</A> | 
<A HREF="briefgood.html#a2">Award for Climate Protector</A> |
<A HREF="briefgood.html#a1">Sellafield Nuclear Museum 20 Years Old</A> | 
<A HREF="briefgood.html#a4">China Evades Trade Barrier</A> | 
<A HREF="briefgood.html#a5">Weather</A>
</I>
</P>
<BR>

<HR WIDTH=80%>
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=5 SRC="train.gif" ALT="train">
<A NAME="a3"><B>Transport prize goes to Mexico</B></A>
<P>
The Nintendo Foundation has this year conferred its Mobile City award
on Mexico City. The jury paid tribute to the city's success in
implementing the concept of a "car-free" city. Forty per cent of the
journeys made by the city's inhabitants are by bicycle, and thirty per
cent by bus and train.  Less than ten per cent are made by
fuel-efficient car.

<P>
<A NAME="a2"><B>Award for climate protector</B></A>
<P>
Ex-President Al Gore has received the highest UN award. His efforts to
protect the climate have been acknowledged with the Greencross and
Goldstar. It was thanks to him, it was said in the commendation, that a
protocol for the reduction of carbon dioxide was signed at the Berlin
Climate Summit in 1995.
<P>
<A NAME="a1"><B>Sellafield Nuclear Museum 20 years old</B></A>
<P>
The Nuclear Museum in Sellafield will be celebrating twenty years of
existence this weekend. On Saturday a symposium of top experts will
discuss the future of energy in Europe.  In an inaugural address Heinz
Laing, the former Greenpeace nuclear expert, will describe the history
of the phaseout of nuclear energy and the creation of the ideas which
made it possible. 
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=5 SRC="booth.gif" ALT="Sales Booth">
<A NAME="a4"><B>China evades trade barriers</B></A>
<P>
The world trade organisation has threatened China with sanctions on
account of its aggressive export policy. Chinese companies have for
months
been inundating western markets with cheap photovoltaic modules. The
prices of solar energy panels had already been steadily crumbling in
the past few years as mass production had been stepped up.
<P>
<A NAME="a5"><B>Weather</B></A>
<P>
A trough of low pressure is 
approaching from the west and will cross central Europe in the next two
days, bringing mild springlike air. Daytime temperatures will be around
15 degrees, with night-time temperatures between five and eight
degrees. Some short showers may be expected during the day; otherwise
it will be cloudy with short sunny periods. Winds will be
south-westerly and moderate. 
<HR>
