<HEAD>
<TITLE>A STATEMENT FROM THE WHITE HOUSE</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="9CFCFC" TEXT="130036" LINK="D51C27" VLINK="970000" ALINK="E200A9">
<table border=1 width=100% cellpadding=10>
<tr><td colspan=2>
<a href="whales.html"><img border=0 ALIGN=right WIDTH=80 HEIGHT=67 src="../icons/biowhai.gif"></a>

<H3>A STATEMENT FROM JAMES BAKER AT THE WHITE HOUSE</H3>

</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<table border=0 cellpadding=20><tr><td>



<P><B>May 17 1996  5:30 pm Washington time</B>


<P><B>Statement of James Baker, Administrator of the National Oceanic 
and Atmospheric Administration and US Commissioner to the 
International Whaling Commission
</B>

<P>Today, the US issued a strong protest against Norway's plans to 
begin commercial whaling next week in the North Atlantic. 

<P>The United States is deeply opposed to commercial whaling, which 
has caused drastic declines in a number of species and driven 
some stocks to near extinction. In 1982, nations from around the 
world imposed a moratorium on on commercial whaling under the 
auspices of the International Whaling Commission (IWC). The 
United States recognises that Norway lodged a formal objection
to  this moratorium, and therefore is technically not bound by
it.  However, the United States reiterated its call today for
Norway  to join the nations of the world in refraining from
whaling.

<P>The United States believes that the process by which Norway 
calculated its quota of 425 minke whales did not have adequate 
international oversight. Norway's quota was issued shortly after 
a meeting of a working group of the IWC's scientific committee 
earlier this month.  The working group developed a consensus 
estimate of the stock of minke whales in the North East Atlantic. 

<P>The United States is committed to science based solutions to 
international environmental problems and it welcomes the working 
group's consensus estimate. However, this estimate has not yet 
been considered by the IWC's scientific committee, which will 
meet to review this matter next month, or by the Commission 
itself. 

<P>The United States is also concerned about reports of illegal 
exports of whale meat from Norway. The United States calls on 
Norway to take strong measures to enforce its export ban. 

<BR><HR><BR>

</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
