<P><head><H4>From:    SV Rainbow Warrior            
<P>Date:    Wed 19-JUL-95 
<P>Subject: Update from RW for Internet Diary </H4></head>
<body>
 
<P>We're 150 miles from Rarotonga, with our ETA there tomorrow
morning at 1000 hours.  We have been invited to an official
function with the Prime Minister, Sir Geoffrey Henry, and
opposition MPs, on Thursday night at which he plans to make a
major announcement about the Cook Islands Government's action on
French testing.  This will be followed on our side by a public
meeting at 8pm on the ship.  On Friday we will be doing some
school talks.
 
<P>We've been wallowing around a bit in choppy seas today, so
queasiness has hit a few of the crew.  But spirits are high as 
we
approach Rarotonga and the famous "Tere's Bar"... the only place
to be on a Friday night in Rarotonga!
 
<P>Richard Leney (mechanic) will leave the ship in Rarotonga to go
to Auckland to help find new zodiacs.  A new mate, Derek 
Nichols,
will be joining us.
 
<P>Our ETD from Rarotonga is Saturday morning, and we are scheduled
to arrive in Fiji one week later, on Saturday 29 July. We've 
been
really encouraged by all the amazing work GP offices have been
doing around the world -- sorry if we haven't had time to 
respond
to you all, but we really appreciate it!  We're also feeling 
good
about the flotilla plans which seem to be shaping up well in New
Zealand and Australia.  Along with the decision to send the MV
Greenpeace to Moruroa too, it looks we'll be giving the French
military something to really worry about soon!
 
<P>Cheers, Stephanie
 
</body></html>


 

 









