 <P>
<P align=right><a href="rw.html"><image align=right src="srwa.gif" border=0 ></a>
<a href="jun23d.html"><image align=right src="irig.gif" border=0 ></a>
<a href="jun22d.html"><image align=right src="ilef.gif" border=0 ></a>

<P><br><br><br><br><br>

<head>







<H4> DIARY UPDATE FROM THE CREW OF THE RAINBOW WARRIOR:
<P>Thursday 22nd JUNE 07:58:59 GMT  Part I.</H4> 
</head>            

<body>





 
<P>As the ocean outside the harbour of Roratanga is to the leeward
(sheltered) side of the island, we make use of the calm waters
for a few hours of more boat training.  It certainly makes a
change from the steep swells we battled further south, and allows
for practice of a different set of manouevres.  Also some good
"man overboard" training, where we practise gettting bodies out
of the water.
 
<P>Some crew remained behind on board where, throughout the course
of the day, several hundred school children of a wide variety of
ages toured the Rainbow Warrior.  It is always a great boost to
the crew to be infected by the enthusiasm of the kids.  Their
clear sense of (in)justice on this issue uncomplicated by
politics or economics: why should anyone want to build bombs that
can kill millions of people all at once, and test it in somebody
else's backyard?  Why indeed.

<P>More as we continue our journey -- Alice.
<br>
<HR>                          

