<head>



<H4>From:    Greenpeace Vessel SV Rainbow Warrior
<br>Date:    Sunday 02-JUL-95 03:01:35 GMT
<br>Subject: Internet diary</H4><body>

<P>The blockade has now been in place for three days.  Tensions have
been building, but it looks as if the barricades will be lifted
today.  Protest marches have also taken place on five other
islands and on Tahiti the marches actually began more than a week
ago and circumnavigated the island.  The people are demanding a
referendum on the subject of a resumption of nuclear testing:  a
fair enough demand, as they are the people who must live with the
immediate and long-term consequences of the testing.  There is
tremendous feeling over this issue and concern for their children
and children to come.
 
<P>For the Rainbow Warrior, apart from active participation in the
various anti-nuclear demonstrations, it is a time for last minute
preparations.  The ship is fully supplied again, to sail for who
knows how long?  Using the medium of the local press, it is made
quite clear to us that the military authorities will not tolerate
the ship entering the military exclusion zone around the atoll. 
What is in store for us remains an open book...
<P>Alice Leney</body></html>


