<P>Date:    WED  2-AUG-95 
<br>Subject: GOOD news from France

<P>An opinion poll released today by the French daily newspaper "Le 
Parisien" gives the following numbers.

<P>A) Do you think Jacques Chirac was right or wrong to decide the 
resumption of French nuclear testing in the Pacific ?

<pre>- he was right : 25 %.
- he was wrong : 56 %;
- no answer : 19 %.</pre>

<P>B) You know that the resumption of nuclear testing has generated a 
certain number of critiques. All in all, do you personally wish that 
Jacques Chirac renounce this decision to resume nuclear testing ?

<pre>- yes : 60 %.
- no : 29 %.
- no answer : 11 %.</pre>

<P>C) If it was proven that nuclear testing can be done without danger 
for the environment, would you be favorable or opposed to having 
the testing take place in France ?

<pre>- favorable : 40 %.
- opposed : 53 %.
- no answer : 7 %.</pre>
