<title>Chronology of Opposition to French Nuclear Testing</title>
</head>

<body>
<h2>Chronology of International Opposition </h2>
<H3>to French Nuclear Testing in the South Pacific </H3>
<p>
<P>A chronology of opposition to France's decision to resume nuclear 
testing at Moruroa atoll since Jacques Chirac was elected President
of France on May 7. The decision sparked international outrage and 
expressions of deep concern from around the world.  Chirac announced
on June 13 that France would conduct more nuclear weapons tests in 
the South Pacific.
<p> 

<ul>
<li><A HREF="testchr1.html">International Opposition prior to France's announcement on June 13</A>
<li><A HREF="testchr2.html">International Opposition since France's announcement on June 13</A>
<li><A HREF="testchr3.html">Statments in favour of the resumption of Nuclear Testing</A>
</ul>



</body></html>
