<html><P align=right> <a href="rw.html"><image align=right src="srwa.gif" border=0 ></a><P><br><br><br><br><br>
<head>
<title>The Mission of the Rainbow Warrior</title>
</head>

<body>
<h2>The Mission of the Rainbow Warrior</h2>

<p>
The mission of the Rainbow Warrior en-route to Moruroa atoll is
two-fold: to mobilise the international community to pressure 
President Chirac to reverse his decision to resume nuclear testing
at Moruroa, and to attempt by non-violent direct action to stop the 
tests.
<p>
Greenpeace believes President Chirac's decision threats to shatter 
an historic window of opportunity to achieve this year -- fifty years 
after the bomb was first 'tested' on the people of Hiroshima and 
Nagasaki -- a comprehensive test ban treaty banning all tests in all 
environments  for all time.  There are a few weeks left before French 
tests are due to resume at Moruroa in September: our aim now is to 
galvanise the force of international public pressure against President 
Chirac's decision and ensure we move nearer to our goal of a nuclear 
free future.
<p>



</body></html>


